  "text": "The Kafka producer TimeoutException with message 'Expiring N record(s) for topic-partition' is triggered by the following components:\n\n1. **TimeoutException Definition** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489): The exception class is defined in `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/TimeoutException.java` at line 22. It extends RetriableException and provides multiple constructors for creating timeout errors.\n\n2. **Record Batch Expiration Logic**: Two key methods implement the expiration mechanism:\n   - `RecordAccumulator.expiredBatches()` (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489, `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java`, line 465): This method iterates through accumulated record batches and identifies those that have reached the delivery timeout using `batch.hasReachedDeliveryTimeout(deliveryTimeoutMs, now)`. It returns a list of expired batches.\n   - `Sender.getExpiredInflightBatches()` (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489, `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java`, line 180): This method checks in-flight batches that have reached the delivery timeout.\n\n3. **Error Message Generation**: The error is thrown in the `sendProducerData()` method (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489, `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java`, lines 405-418). When batches expire, the method creates the error message \"Expiring [recordCount] record(s) for [topicPartition]: [elapsed time] ms has passed since batch creation\" and throws a new TimeoutException with this message via `failBatch()` at line 418.\n\n4. **Configuration Constant**: The `delivery.timeout.ms` configuration is defined in `ProducerConfig.java` (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489, `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerConfig.java`, line 165) as the constant `DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`. The configuration documentation explains that it sets an upper bound on the time to report success or failure after a call to `send()` returns, which controls when record batches are considered expired."
}

